<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-ADOH4ZhWTiOndz_c5X0ShA" name=",_zeUKUJ6KEeCHFd5_MqJHKQ" guid="-ADOH4ZhWTiOndz_c5X0ShA" changeDate="2011-08-24T04:59:40.881-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architecture metrics to be analyzed are the single point and the latent fault metrics that were specified in the HW&#xD;
    specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The scope of this analysis is limited to the electrical and electronic parts, only electrical failure modes and failure&#xD;
    rates are considered for electro-mechanical parts.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Compliance with the HW architectural metrics specified shall be achieved for each safety goal the item is involved in.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If combining applicable safety goals then the target metric of the safety goal with the highest metric shall be&#xD;
    considered.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is advised that the user refers to ISO 26262 Volume 5, clause 8 for details of the objectives, requirements and&#xD;
    methods&amp;nbsp;relating to architecture metrics.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is recommended that users refer to ISO 26262, volume 5 annex&amp;nbsp;C for further information regarding HW architectural&#xD;
    metrics and annex D for evaluation of the diagnostic coverage (this annex has a large number of tables that help with&#xD;
    identification of possible random HW failures). Appendix E and F are also very informative regarding the use of&#xD;
    architectural metrics.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To determine how well the HW design will meet the architecture metrics.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
